		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://scottsbasslessons.com/?p=1200#comment-2035</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Hi Thomas... is chord tone is just a note that exists within a certain chord. So for instance the chord of C major is made from 3 notes - C, E, G - they are the chord tones. Here&#039;s another example... Dm7 is made from the notes D, F, G, Bb - those are the chord tones of that chord. Hope that helps man. S ;)]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi Thomas&#8230; is chord tone is just a note that exists within a certain chord. So for instance the chord of C major is made from 3 notes &#8211; C, E, G &#8211; they are the chord tones. Here&#8217;s another example&#8230; Dm7 is made from the notes D, F, G, Bb &#8211; those are the chord tones of that chord. Hope that helps man. S ;)</p>
]]></content:encoded>
